A man on Thursday night hanged himself after killing his 3-year -old daughter following a domestic dispute with his wife.Musee Nzoka is said to have had a bitter exchange with the wife, a saloonist at Itivanzou market. The wife took off when he threatened to slash her with a panga. She left her daughter behind.A witness said Nzoka, in his early 30s, hanged his daughter on a tree in his neighbour Musyoka Kakuli s farm, before hanging himself in a different branch of the same tree. Police took the two bodies to the mortuary.The incident took place in Kyandani village in Kamuwongo location of Kyuso district. About a fortnight ago, assistant chief Mutinda Mwinzi was found dead in his house. His body was found hanging from the roof.